## 7. Conclusion

We identify an infinite ladder of exact dimensional identities linking odd-dimensional unit-ball volumes to squared even-dimensional unit-ball volumes. The family

\[
V_{4n+1} = \frac{2^{2n+1} (n!)^2}{(4n+1)!!} \, V_{2n}^2
\]

reveals a previously unnoticed “double-square crossing” structure. The first nontrivial crossing occurs at dimension 9, where geometric squaring and prime multiplicity appear simultaneously.

This provides a new perspective on the organization of hypersphere volumes and the emergence of multiplicity within odd-dimensional volume ladders.

